HEADWORD: Miscolor
<hw>Mis*col"or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To give a wrong
color to.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <mark>[figuratively]</mark> <def>To set forth erroneously
or unfairly; to misrepresent; <as>as, to <ex>miscolor</ex>
facts</as>.</def> <rj><au>C. Kingsley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Miscomfort</ent>⟦br⟧
